7.10	Scott_Corbett	Scott Corbett	W. Scott Corbett (b. July 27, 1913 in Kansas City, Missouri; d. March 6, 2006 in Providence, Rhode Island) was an American novelist and educator. He wrote a total of 89 books; he began with five adult novels, then began writing books for children, eventually writing sixty-nine such books. His best known book is The Lemonade Trick, a novel for children. One of his books, entitled The Reluctant Landlord (1950), was made into the 1951 film Love Nest. He wrote his first children's book, Susie Sneakers, in 1956.	
